[1] Cholera - India (Mombai)
Date: Sun 3 Jul 2011
Source: DNA India [edited]
http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/report_monsoon-woes-2-kids-test-positive-for-cholera-in-mumbai_1561729


Mumbai is reeling from many cases of waterborne diseases like
jaundice, diarrhea, and gastroenteritis; now cholera has also been
added to that list. Two children have tested positive at the Sion
hospital on Fri 1 Jul 2011.

"The samples of the 2 children have shown the presence of the cholera
organism. One is from Antop Hill and the other from Bhiwandi. They are
presently being treated, and both are recuperating," confirmed a
senior doctor from the Sion hospital. Their reports have been sent to
Kasturba hospital. The patients were hospitalized with complaints of
vomiting, diarrhea, and stomach cramps. Doctors treating them said
that they exhibited classic symptoms of cholera, like sunken eyes,
stomach ache, and severe dehydration.

[byline: Somita Pal]

