******
[5] Cholera - India (Kerala)
Date: Sat 2 Jul 2011
Source: AsiaNetIndia [edited]
http://www.asianetindia.com/news/cholera-cases-rise-wayanad_281985.html


As many as 114 people have been admitted in the several hospitals in
Wayanad district with symptoms of cholera on Sat 2 Jul 2011. The
official reports reveal that the patients who have been admitted in
the hospital from 13 colonies in the district were suffering from
cholera.

The condition of 5 people who are under treatment at Kozhikode
medical college hospital with symptoms of cholera is reported to be
critical. It was confirmed after a medical test at the Kozhikode
Medical College Hospital that the patients were suffering from
cholera, Neetha Vijayan, district medical officer, said.

Around 7 people have succumbed to the disease. Preventive measures,
including chlorination of drinking water every 3 days, had been taken
in tribal colonies in the area.

